               <physDesc>
                  <objectDesc form="codex">
                     <supportDesc material="chart">
                        <support>
                           <material>Indian paper (?). 
                              Prefaces are not ruled or illuminated.  Paper is chickpea, well-burnished. Hand of main
                              text seems to be the same as earlier parts of codex.</material>
                        </support><extent>456 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="cm">
                           <height/>
                           <width/>
                        </dimensions>
                           <dimensions type="written" unit="cm">
                              <height/>
                              <width/>
                           </dimensions>
                        </extent>
                        
                        <foliation><p>Foliated with Roman numerals throughout and with Persian
                              numerals in red only in the main text (starting on f.32, marked in red
                              f.1). The final folio (f.456) is marked f.425 in red.</p></foliation>
                        <collation>
                           <p>ff.1-7r contain first preface, ending with a note stating that it
                              contains a preface composed and copied in 1038 by ʿAbd al-Laṭīf
                              (entitled Mirʾāt al-Ḥadāʾiq). ff.7v-13r (in same hand) contain a
                              detailed fihrist (table of contents) with folios numbers (created by
                              the same person who wrote the Preface). f.13v has a poem with a note
                              saying this is not found in many manuscript but is added here.
                              ff.14v-18v contain a second preface about the commentary (completion
                              date: 1040H, f.18v). f.19r ʿAbd al-Laṭīf explains there follows the
                              preface by Sanāʾī. ff.19v-26v preface of Sana’i with interlinear
                              commentary of ʿAbd al-Laṭīf. ff.27r-30r another detailed fihrist in
                              red (with folio numbers in black). ff.30v-32r = blank pages. f.32v
                              marks the start of the main text with an illuminated heading (here
                              begins the second set of foliation in red ink).</p>
                        </collation><condition>First few folios and some later have been
                           repaired. Red rubrications. Moderate worm damage and staining.</condition>
                     </supportDesc>
                     <layoutDesc>

                        <layout n="1" columns="1" ruledLines="0">
                           <p>Main text is ruled in sparkling
                              gold with lapis.</p>
                           <dimensions type="line-height" unit="mm"/>
                        </layout>
                     </layoutDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <handDesc>

                     <handNote scope="major" script="nasta_liq" medium="black"> Beautiful Indian nastaʿlīq. Qur’anic verses in naskh.. Scribe:
                           <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="" role="scr">Saʿd Allāh Ibrāhīm
                           Ābādī</persName>.</handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                     <decoNote type="other"> Illuminated heading (sarlauh) at start of main text <locus from="32v" to="32v">f.32v</locus></decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions><list><item><label>Marginalia</label> Marginal comments
                     throughout, mostly marked لط – presumably for ʿAbd
                     al-Laṭīf</item></list>
