                  <acquisition>Gift of <persName key="">Edward Ephraim Pote (d.1832)
                     </persName> in <date calendar="#Gregorian">1788</date>. The "Pote Collection"
                     arrived in England from India in <date calendar="#Gregorian">1790</date> and
                     was divided between the Colleges of Eton and King's, Cambridge, with the first
                     half alphabetically going to King's. Both halves of the collection are now
                     housed in Cambridge University Library on permanent loan. Most if not all of
                     the manuscripts had previously been owned by <persName key="person_7537069"
                        >Colonel Antoine-Louis Henri Polier (1741–1795)</persName>.</acquisition>
